      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SIR ZINO (10) showed little early speed last start and failed to come on in the straight when eighth, beaten 12 lengths, over 2200m at Grafton. Finds a nice race and can turn things around in this grade. FARRAIGE (7) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1750m at Muswellbrook, beaten 8 lengths into 11th. Perfectly placed and is sure to play a major role. MY PEPPERJACK (3) settled well back when 4 lengths from the winner in tenth over 1812m at this track last start, a less impressive effort than her seventh at Taree the run before. Has the class to find the winners' list. ROCK THE MACHINE (2) turned things around last start and landed the prize by half a length over 1900m at Armidale. Well placed to feature in the finish again.",
